    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="468"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 2, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 63.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to hand you herewith, for your information
                    and such immediate action as you may deem advisable, copy of a letter just
                    received from E. Atkins &amp; Co., Boston, Mass.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <gloss type="from">E. Atkins &amp; Co</gloss>. to
                            Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Boston, Mass.</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-01">
                                <hi rend="italic">January 1, 1896</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: We are informed through confidential but
                        reliable source that it is the intention of the Cuban agents in New York to
                        destroy the buildings and machinery at our estate, Soledad, situated near
                        Cienfuegos, Cuba.</p>
                    <p>We beg to lay this information before the State Department, with the
                        suggestion that the same be transmitted through the Spanish minister to the
                        authorities in Cuba, in order that they may be promptly advised and prepared
                        to guard against a possible attack by the insurgents.</p>
                    <p>We remain, etc.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Atkins</hi> &amp; Co.</closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
